@outscale-mgo I went ahead and merged this PR into trunk, but I think some tests are strongly needed, especially since it appears there are no existing tests for this driver right now (so no wonder this issue was not caught earlier).

If you plan to contribute bigger changes, please also make sure you sign an ICLA - https://libcloud.readthedocs.io/en/latest/development.html#contributing-bigger-changes.

Thanks.

I've added test case in 8752aa52320574a96fc11a0ce71c12054910e86f and merged PR into trunk.

@shepilov-vladislav Next time if you want PR to be merged, please include a corresponding unit (regression) test case. 

Thanks.

@rsnk96 

1. Yeah, I think it makes sense. But since queuing APIs are usually quite poll heavy, I think it also makes sense to expse async API in addition to the sync one.
2. ICLA is a good start. We have some project specific information here - https://libcloud.readthedocs.io/en/stable/development.html
